Fibrolamellar carcinoma of the liver: radiologic-pathologic correlation. Fibrolamellar carcinoma is a malignant hepatocellular tumor with distinct clinical and pathologic differences from hepatocellular carcinoma. It differs from hepatocellular carcinoma in demographics, condition of the affected liver, tumor markers, and prognosis. Fibrolamellar carcinoma characteristically manifests as a large hepatic mass in adolescents or young adults (without gender predominance). Cirrhosis elevated alpha-fetoprotein levels